FBIS4-9969 "drlat066_k_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina Interior Minister Rules Out Jujuy Intervention `Now' Interior Minister Rules Out Jujuy Intervention `Now' PY0504125294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 0155 GMT 5 Apr 94 PY0504125294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS Spanish BFN [Text] Buenos Aires, 4 Apr (NA) -- Interior Minister Carlos Ruckauf on 4 April ruled out the possibility of government intervention in Jujuy Province "for now." Ruckauf said: "The situation in Jujuy is very complex, but it is not a province with structural problems. Therefore, for now, there will be no federal measures." The minister made these remarks shortly before attending a dinner that Carlos Corach, the Justicialist Party's No. 1 candidate for Constituent Assembly member for the federal capital, hosted for 600 entrepreneurs at the Alvear Palace Hotel in this capital.
